<b>Subject:</b> Keep HPs up and work in teams<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1006" TARGET=_self>Re: Rating on how I feel whos who on PvP server..</A> (Lenix)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>

<BR>Even though my region is very player friendly right now, I am making it a point to keep my hit points high on the PvP server. Likewise it is adviseable to group or have friends nearby. Dropping even 2 bars of health is ill-advised on a PvP server. This may mean levelling slower but considering the alternatives it's a price I'm willing to pay. No more hunting yellow monsters for me!
<P>The Black
<P>&gt; Your number 5, Jander, is pretty lame. He came after me becuase
<BR>&gt; he noticed that I was down to only a couple of HP left after a
<BR>&gt; battle with some Gnoll's.. he would rather have an easy kill
<BR>&gt; than a fight. I'm a newbie to the whole PK scene, but I would
<BR>&gt; concider that as pretty damn lame. :P
<P>&gt; - Lenix
<BR>
